  "text": "Although the in situ hybridisation for sc revealed functional divergence between homologous DCEs (Figure 2 ), only double stainings performed at cellular resolution can provide an accurate comparison of enhancer activity. It has previously been shown that the Dm-DCE drives the expression of a cytoplasmic form of ß-Gal in cells of the DC proneural cluster [CITATION_1] . We have used this lacZ reporter line as an internal reference, and compared it to other DCEs driving the expression of a nuclear form of GFP. In addition to Dq-DCE and Dv-DCE, we have included the DCE from D. eugracilis (De-DCE), whose phylogenetic position is closer to D. melanogaster ( Figure 1 ) [CITATION_2] [CITATION_3] .",
